self.setUpClass()
num_qubits = 2
p = ql.Program('test_usingqx_sparse2qubitotherqubit', platform, num_qubits)
k = ql.Kernel('akernel', platform, num_qubits)
matrix = [0.30279949 - 0.60010283j, 0.0 + 0.0j, -0.58058628 - 0.45946559j, 
    0.0 - 0.0j, 0.0 + 0.0j, 0.30279949 - 0.60010283j, 0.0 - 0.0j, -
    0.58058628 - 0.45946559j, 0.04481146 - 0.73904059j, 0.0 + 0.0j, 
    0.64910478 + 0.17456782j, 0.0 + 0.0j, 0.0 + 0.0j, 0.04481146 - 
    0.73904059j, 0.0 + 0.0j, 0.64910478 + 0.17456782j]
u1 = ql.Unitary('sparse2_qubit_unitary_other_qubit', matrix)
u1.decompose()
k.gate(u1, [0, 1])
p.add_kernel(k)
p.compile()
qx.set(os.path.join(output_dir, p.name + '_initialqasmwriter_out.qasm'))
qx.execute()
c0 = qx.get_state()
self.assertAlmostEqual(helper_prob(matrix[0]), helper_regex(c0)[0], 5)
self.assertAlmostEqual(helper_prob(matrix[4]), 0, 5)
self.assertAlmostEqual(helper_prob(matrix[8]), helper_regex(c0)[1], 5)
self.assertAlmostEqual(helper_prob(matrix[12]), 0, 5)
